The paper deals with problems related to Lie algebras, which have applications in various areas of computer science such as differential equations, particle physics, group theory, and complexity theory. The paper presents algorithms for solving certain cases of Lie algebra conjugacy, which are related to problems such as graph isomorphism, code equivalence, and affine equivalence of polynomials. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry), which are both relevant to algorithmic aspects of the paper. The paper also involves group theory, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with complexity theory, which could lead to it being categorized under cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
